metadata.name: Vormenspel #77
metadata.description:
Schetsboek contained an algorithm that scribbled a small piece of art (800x800 px).

In this artwork, I used that algorithm in two systems (in a grid and/or layered), taking it to new dimensions, but still focused on composition and the interplay of simple shapes and colors. 

It reminds me to stay playful and enjoy the little things in life.  

This is a free mint for holders of schetsboek.

metadata.name: Urban Building: Where Are We Going? #129
metadata.description:
This is a building generation made by pure code.

Urbanization at the almost everywhere in the world has stepped into an accelerating phase in last century. Buildings bring magnificent achievements and represent the human power over nature. But, following these tall and crowd buildings one by one, where are we going?

In this work, I generate different types of building with a special viewpoint, which represent different concepts of states we are going to. Hope you enjoy these varieties and coincidences.

Variables:
- 4 modes
- 4 environments
- 3 orbs
- 3 building density
- 3 building structures

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Sand Shapes #36
metadata.description:
An experiment in line texture by Nate Donato, this piece features lines composed of a sand-like particle texture.  Bounds around line generation properties were set loosely, resulting in many possible line characters with unique weights, wobbles, and more.  Lines are generated in individual layered segments one by one, resulting in a pleasing animation of gradual composition as they compose one of twelve possible shapes, in one of eight possible color schemes.  

Each "line" is made up of thousands of points, and so rendering the live view of this piece may be computer intensive.  As an added bonus a small amount of proprietary line data is emitted to the development console, allowing the minted collection to serve as a palette of potential line qualities for the artist to use in future works.  Any owners of pieces used in this way by the artist on future projects will be granted a share of said future project's royalties.

In active live view, press [1] to view medium res, [2] to view high res, and [0] to return to original viewport width view.

Written in vanilla JavaScript without the use of external libraries.

metadata.name: 10SCII #210
metadata.description:
10SCII is my take on the famous 10 PRINT program.

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1)); : GOTO 10 is a single line program that produces a simple but visually appealing set of forward and backward slashes.

This project riffs on the original idea by removing the vertical space between lines and widening the horizontal gap. This changes the produced pieces from a maze of slashes into a series of towers. This is then rendered and animated as ASCII.

Visit https://10print.org/ to learn more about the original program that inspired this piece.

metadata.name: Waves and Ripples #17
metadata.description:
Waves and Ripples is an implementation of a continuous CA, where wave like behaviours are obtained from the influence of neighbour cells over the cell itself. Depeding on the connections config for each cell, different patterns will emerge, creating waves, ripples, or a mix of both. When single loop is on, the calculations and drawings are done at once, which makes for a more chaotic visual.
Best enjoyed in full-screen :) 

Click anywhere to restart

Features : 
  shrinkFactor : 3 types
  connectArray: 16 possibilities,
  extraConnection: 4 types,
  mutualNeighbour: 40% chance,
  singleLoop: 30% chance
  monoChromo:  15% chance

Inspired by Matt Pearson's book.

metadata.name: Physarum Logo #46
metadata.description:
These past few months have been a great experience and with the beta ending, I wanted to create a piece to thank all collectors and pay tribute to this great platform. 

The piece is based on a physarum simulation with a couple of tweaks, such as continuous behavioural changes and an extra information layer that further manipulates the physarum.

There are ~262k particles simulated in parallel, so it is quite GPU heavy. 

Each piece features one of 12 different colour pallets, the text and a couple of cell-like bodies running around the screen.

Controls: 
S - Save image
H - Hide Text
Click/Touch - Spawn particles

Disclaimer: This is nothing official by the platform itself, merely a tribute by an artist and fan. 

With all that said: Thank you to everyone, and see you in 1.0 !

metadata.name: Alcyone #180
metadata.description:
And the ragged rock in the restless waters,
Waves wash over it, fogs conceal it;
On a halcyon day it is merely a monument,
In navigable weather it is always a seamark
To lay a course by: but in the sombre season
Or the sudden fury, is what it always was.

THE DRY SALVAGES
